      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOTS OF HEART (3) won at Redcliffe two runs ago before finishing third at his latest appearance over 1660m at this track, beaten 5 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Certainly cannot be faulted after that last effort. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. BENNYDASOOK (6) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 5.5 metres from the winner in fifth over 2280m at Redcliffe. Finds a suitable assignment and can grab a well-deserved win. PICCOLO DIAVOLO (1) is right in contention after finishing in the placings for the second time in a row last start, beaten a nose into second at Redcliffe. No reason he cannot take this out. GIRL POWER (7) last appeared when fourth over 1660m at this track six months ago. Must be respected.",
